teil gelegt.  aThis book provides a detailed introduction to Romance linguistics, giving valuable information on 1) working techniques and tools, 2) the sub-disciplines of linguistics, and 3) Romance languages, thus linking theoretical reflection with practical skills. The book is divided into 13 identically structured units (including working techniques, branches of linguistics, and language outlines) that provide a condensed introduction to the field. Particular focus is placed on the extensive exercise section.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEuropean literaturexRenaissance, 1450-1600. 0aLITERARY CRITICISMxEuropeanxFrench. 0aRomance literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aEinführung. 4aLinguistik. 4aRomanistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLinguistics.  aMethodology.  aRomance Studies.1 aPöll, Bernhard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRainer, Franz, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK 2013z9783110317237oZDB-23-DSP0 cprintz978311031013940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311031069640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110310696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110310696/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2013